message: To get 100 points, you need to combine one processed mundane item with one processed magical item. 'Processing' means using the vial on solid items to 'extract' them, or using the filter on liquid items to 'filter' them. Once you have an extracted/filtered mundane item and an extracted/filtered magical item, combine them. Avoid trying to filter solid items or extract liquid items as this doesn't work. Also, combining with gas items often leads to low values unless specific steps are followed for 'only mundane' paths, which seems less reliable than the 'one magical, one mundane' path. Focus on getting extracted solids and filtered liquids, then combine one of each type.

message: The primary path to 100 points is to use the 'vial' on solid items (extracts) and the 'filter' on liquid items (filtered). Then, combine one 'processed' magical item (extracted or filtered) with one 'processed' mundane item (extracted or filtered). Be cautious with 'gas/vapor' items; if it's a magical gas, the 'extract mundane + expose to gas + filter' path may only yield 80 points, not 100, unlike when only mundane items are present.
